<html prefix="dc: http://purl.org/dc/terms/ mw: http://mediawiki.org/rdf/" about="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:Redirect/revision/884000610"><head prefix="mwr: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:Redirect/"><meta property="mw:TimeUuid" content="bc23d3c0-3a75-11e9-9d48-8dd0d2c34200"/><meta charset="utf-8"/><meta property="mw:pageNamespace" content="0"/><meta property="mw:pageId" content="30994"/><link rel="dc:replaces" resource="mwr:revision/881302651"/><meta property="dc:modified" content="2019-02-18T22:53:20.000Z"/><meta property="mw:revisionSHA1" content="99b24be1e6d201d53d482497a462e5865ecffca6"/><meta property="mw:html:version" content="2.1.0"/><link rel="dc:isVersionOf" href="//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Theravada"/><title>Theravada</title><base href="//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"/><link rel="stylesheet" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/load.php?modules=mediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmediawiki.skinning.content.parsoid%7Cmediawiki.skinning.interface%7Cskins.vector.styles%7Csite.styles%7Cext.cite.style%7Cext.cite.styles%7Cmediawiki.page.gallery.styles&amp;only=styles&amp;skin=vector"/><!--[if lt IE 9]><script src="//en.wikipedia.org/w/load.php?modules=html5shiv&amp;only=scripts&amp;skin=vector&amp;sync=1"></script><script>html5.addElements('figure-inline');</script><![endif]--><meta http-equiv="content-language" content="en"/><meta http-equiv="vary" content="Accept"/></head><body id="mwAA" lang="en" class="mw-content-ltr sitedir-ltr ltr mw-body-content parsoid-body mediawiki mw-parser-output" dir="ltr"><section data-mw-section-id="0" id="mwAQ"><div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable" about="#mwt1" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"About","href":"./Template:About"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"How the modern Buddhist school gave rise from the &apos;&apos;&apos;Mahāvihāra Tāmraparṇīya&apos;&apos;&apos; school of [[Vibhajyavāda|Vibhajyavāda Sthaviravāda]] (or &apos;&apos;Vibhajjavāda Theravāda&apos;&apos;) Buddhism"},"2":{"wt":"the early Buddhist school, commonly known as Theravāda in Pali and sometimes in English, that both Theravada (fully) and Mahayana (partially) gave rise from"},"3":{"wt":"Sthaviravāda"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAg">This article is about How the modern Buddhist school gave rise from the <b>Mahāvihāra Tāmraparṇīya</b> school of <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Vibhajyavāda" title="Vibhajyavāda">Vibhajyavāda Sthaviravāda</a> (or <i>Vibhajjavāda Theravāda</i>) Buddhism. For the early Buddhist school, commonly known as Theravāda in Pali and sometimes in English, that both Theravada (fully) and Mahayana (partially) gave rise from, see <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Sthaviravāda" title="Sthaviravāda" class="mw-redirect">Sthaviravāda</a>.</div>
<div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable" about="#mwt2" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"Redirect","href":"./Template:Redirect"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"Tāmraparnīya"},"2":{"wt":"the pre-&apos;&apos;&apos;Mahāvihāra&apos;&apos;&apos; Tāmraparṇīya school based in the [[Abhayagiri Buddhist Monastery]] that adopted [[Mahayana sutras]] with Sthaviravāda and was purged in 3rd century in Sri Lanka"},"3":{"wt":"Abhayagirivāsin (Tāmraparṇīya school)"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAw">"Tāmraparnīya" redirects here. For the pre-<b>Mahāvihāra</b> Tāmraparṇīya school based in the <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Abhayagiri_Buddhist_Monastery" title="Abhayagiri Buddhist Monastery">Abhayagiri Buddhist Monastery</a> that adopted <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Mahayana_sutras" title="Mahayana sutras">Mahayana sutras</a> with Sthaviravāda and was purged in 3rd century in Sri Lanka, see <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Abhayagirivāsin_(Tāmraparṇīya_school)" title="Abhayagirivāsin (Tāmraparṇīya school)" class="new">Abhayagirivāsin (Tāmraparṇīya school)</a>.</div>
<figure typeof="mw:Image/Thumb" id="mwBA"><a href="./File:Phra_Ajan_Jerapunyo-Abbot_of_Watkungtaphao..jpg" id="mwBQ"><img resource="./File:Phra_Ajan_Jerapunyo-Abbot_of_Watkungtaphao..jpg" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d3/Phra_Ajan_Jerapunyo-Abbot_of_Watkungtaphao..jpg/300px-Phra_Ajan_Jerapunyo-Abbot_of_Watkungtaphao..jpg" data-file-width="1600" data-file-height="1200" data-file-type="bitmap" height="225" width="300" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d3/Phra_Ajan_Jerapunyo-Abbot_of_Watkungtaphao..jpg/600px-Phra_Ajan_Jerapunyo-Abbot_of_Watkungtaphao..jpg 2x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d3/Phra_Ajan_Jerapunyo-Abbot_of_Watkungtaphao..jpg/450px-Phra_Ajan_Jerapunyo-Abbot_of_Watkungtaphao..jpg 1.5x" id="mwBg"/></a><figcaption id="mwBw">Theravādin <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Buddhist_monasticism" title="Buddhist monasticism" id="mwCA">monk</a> <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Buddhist_meditation#Theravada_tradition" title="Buddhist meditation" id="mwCQ">meditating</a> while seated in the <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Lotus_position" title="Lotus position" id="mwCg">Lotus position</a> beside <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Sirikit_Dam" title="Sirikit Dam" id="mwCw">Sirikit Dam</a> (<a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Thailand" title="Thailand" id="mwDA">Thailand</a>)</figcaption></figure>
